Pizza Order System
  Create a GUI application titled "Pizza Order System" that allows users to customize their pizza order. The application should include the following components:
  The following is the detailed list of components:
  • Choice
    o Name - pizzaSizeChoice
    o Options - Small, Medium, Large
    o Purpose - Allows the user to select the size of the pizza.
  • Choice
    o Name - pizzaToppingsChoice
    o Options - Mushrooms, Pepperoni, Onions
    o Purpose - Allows the user to select the toppings for the pizza.
  • Choice
    o Name - extraCheeseChoice
    o Options - Yes, No
    o Purpose - Allows the user to choose whether to add extra cheese to the pizza.
  • Label
    o Name - totalLabel
    o Purpose - Displays the total price of the pizza.
  • Button
    o Name - calculateButton
    o Text - "Calculate Total"
    o Functionality - When clicked, calculates the total price of the pizza based on the selected options and displays it in the totalLabel.
  Notes:
  • The pricing rules are as follows:
    o Small pizza (S): $10
    o Medium pizza (M): $15
    o Large pizza (L): $20
  • Each topping adds $2 to the total. If "Extra Cheese" is selected, it adds an additional
  $3.
  • Use setName() to set the names of the components. Variable names do not count as
  the name.
